articles.author: Pamela McClintock
articles.title: Box Office: ‘Captain America’ Leads Slowest Oscar Weekend in Years, ‘Last Breath’ Opens to $7.8M - Hollywood Reporter
articles.description: With no new big titles on the marque and most of the top nominated pictures now available in the home, Marvel's superhero pic easily stayed atop the chart in its third outing with $15 million.
articles.content:
Oscar weekend was a bust at the box office this year. 
Overall domestic revenue is estimated to come in between $56 million and $57 million, the lowest by a long shot in at least a decade, according… [+3907 chars]
